1
00:01:11,206 --> 00:01:14,169
M really doesn't mind you make a little extra money on the side, Dryden.

2
00:01:14,210 --> 00:01:17,203
She just prefer if it wasn't sense secrets.

3
00:01:27,206 --> 00:01:31,201
If this theatric is supposed to scare me, you have the wrong man, Bond.

4
00:01:31,949 --> 00:01:35,206
If M was so sure I was bent, -

5
00:01:35,206 --> 00:01:37,856
-she would have sent an 00.

6
00:01:37,896 --> 00:01:43,206
As being section chief, I'd known if anyone had been permitted 00 status.

7
00:01:45,208 --> 00:01:49,466
- Your file's showing no kills, but it takes ... - Two.

8
00:02:06,204 --> 00:02:10,422
Shame. We barely got to know each other.

9
00:02:14,204 --> 00:02:17,198
I know where you keep your gun.

10
00:02:17,896 --> 00:02:20,202
So I've learned something.

11
00:02:20,930 --> 00:02:23,610
True.

12
00:02:23,944 --> 00:02:28,181
- How did he die? - Your contact? Not well.

13
00:03:12,196 --> 00:03:14,189
Made you feel it, did it?

14
00:03:19,407 --> 00:03:23,190
Well, you needn't worry, the second ...

15
00:03:27,185 --> 00:03:30,846
Yes. Considerably.

16
00:06:14,192 --> 00:06:17,014
007 STATUS CONFIRMED

17
00:07:17,403 --> 00:07:21,317
So, how do I trust this man that I've never met with my money?

18
00:07:21,357 --> 00:07:26,161
They ask for the introduction. That's all my organisation will garuantee.

19
00:08:05,150 --> 00:08:10,297
I suppose our friend, Mr White.. that I've provided the bank services -

20
00:08:10,338 --> 00:08:13,443
- for many other freedom fighters over the years.

21
00:08:17,154 --> 00:08:22,414
- Do you believe in God, Mr. Le Chiffre? - No.

22
00:08:22,444 --> 00:08:25,205
I believe in a reasonable rate of eternety.

23
00:08:25,245 --> 00:08:28,654
- I want no risk on the portefolio. - Agreed.

24
00:08:28,694 --> 00:08:32,032
- And I can access it anywhere in the world? - Yes.

25
00:08:50,196 --> 00:08:53,938
I have the money, so sell my Skyfleet stock.

26
00:08:54,140 --> 00:08:58,257
Sir, you must know you're betting against the market.

27
00:08:58,297 --> 00:09:01,978
Noone expect these shares to go anywhere else but up.

28
00:09:01,999 --> 00:09:04,001
Just do it.

29
00:09:38,458 --> 00:09:42,302
Looks like our man. Burnt scare on his fist.

30
00:09:43,141 --> 00:09:46,034
I wonder if bomb makers are insured against this.

31
00:10:00,132 --> 00:10:02,125
He is on the move.

32
00:10:02,165 --> 00:10:04,309
He's heading straight on me.

33
00:10:05,462 --> 00:10:08,375
- Stop touching your ear.  - Sorry?

34
00:10:08,405 --> 00:10:09,872
Put your hand down!

35
00:10:15,879 --> 00:10:18,630
Toss that bloody weapon, I need him alive.

36
00:17:49,792 --> 00:17:51,795
Listen to me.

37
00:19:32,780 --> 00:19:36,613
Wheeping blood comes from a disarrangement of the lachrymal duct.

38
00:19:37,907 --> 00:19:39,910
Nothing seriously.

39
00:19:48,365 --> 00:19:52,825
I have two pairs, and you have a 17,4 % schance of making a Straight.

40
00:20:16,542 --> 00:20:19,070
BRITISH GOVERNMENT AGENT KILLS UNARMED PRISONER

41
00:20:19,252 --> 00:20:21,599
When does Ellipsis expire?

42
00:20:21,629 --> 00:20:24,046
We have less than 36 hours ...

43
00:20:24,926 --> 00:20:28,628
No, no, that's all the time I have in, mate.

44
00:20:29,265 --> 00:20:31,743
Let our guests have 5 minutes to leave.

45
00:20:31,783 --> 00:20:34,049
Or throw them overboard.

46
00:20:45,052 --> 00:20:47,004
Who the hell do they think that they are?

47
00:20:47,045 --> 00:20:51,009
Even the Prime Minister is smart enought to not ask questions about what we do.

48
00:20:51,040 --> 00:20:54,933
Have you ever seed such a buch of self rightous ass covering frings?

49
00:20:54,974 --> 00:20:57,866
They don't care what we do, they only care about what we get photographed doing.

50
00:20:57,897 --> 00:21:00,435
And how the hell could Bond be so studpid?

51
00:21:00,466 --> 00:21:04,521
I give him 00 status and he celebrates by shooting up an embassy.

52
00:21:04,551 --> 00:21:06,079
And where the hell is he?

53
00:21:06,119 --> 00:21:10,387
In the old days, when they did something that embarassing,they had the good sense to defect.

54
00:21:10,428 --> 00:21:12,046
Christ, I miss the cold war.

55
00:22:26,038 --> 00:22:29,962
- You got a bloody cheek. - Sorry.

56
00:22:29,992 --> 00:22:33,724
- I'll shoot the camera next time. - Or yourself.

57
00:22:33,754 --> 00:22:35,787
Yoy stormed into an embassy.

58
00:22:35,817 --> 00:22:40,166
You violated the only absolute rule in international relationships.

59
00:22:40,187 --> 00:22:42,462
And why? So you could kill a nobody.

60
00:22:42,493 --> 00:22:44,991
We wanted to question him, not to kill him.

61
00:22:45,021 --> 00:22:48,035
For God's sake, you're supposed to display a sense of judgement.

62
00:22:48,065 --> 00:22:50,189
I did.

63
00:22:50,230 --> 00:22:53,031
I thought to extinct a bombmaker would be a good thing.

64
00:22:53,061 --> 00:22:54,993
One bombmaker.

65
00:22:55,034 --> 00:22:58,027
We're trying to find out how an entire group of terrorists are financed, -

66
00:22:58,058 --> 00:23:01,031
- and you give us one bombmaker.

67
00:23:02,032 --> 00:23:04,025
The man isn't even a true believer.

68
00:23:04,055 --> 00:23:05,855
He is a gun for hire.

69
00:23:05,896 --> 00:23:10,831
And thanks to your over developed trigger finger we have no idea of who hired him or why.

70
00:23:10,861 --> 00:23:15,028
- And where the hell did you find out where I lived? - Same way I found out your name.

71
00:23:15,059 --> 00:23:21,026
- I had no idea what M stood for ... - Utter one more sylabelle and I'll have you killed.

72
00:23:22,027 --> 00:23:25,021
I knew it was too early to promote you.

73
00:23:25,051 --> 00:23:28,024
And I understand 00's have a very short life expectancy

74
00:23:29,026 --> 00:23:32,019
So your mistake will be very short lived.

75
00:23:38,603 --> 00:23:41,981
Bond, this is maybe too much for a blunt instrument to understand.

76
00:23:42,022 --> 00:23:46,027
- but arrogance and self awareness seldom go hand in hand.

77
00:23:46,057 --> 00:23:48,889
So you want me to be half munk and half hitman?

78
00:23:48,919 --> 00:23:53,025
Any munk can kill. I want you to take your ego out of the equation.

79
00:23:53,056 --> 00:23:55,979
And to judge the situation dispassionately.

80
00:23:56,747 --> 00:24:01,086
I have to know if I can trust you.. and to know that you know who to trust.

81
00:24:01,116 --> 00:24:04,616
Since I don't know that, I need you out of my sight.

82
00:24:04,646 --> 00:24:08,024
Stick your head in the sand and think about your future.

83
00:24:08,044 --> 00:24:11,028
Because these bastards want your head, -

84
00:24:11,068 --> 00:24:15,013
- and I am seriously considering feeding you to them.

85
00:24:21,910 --> 00:24:24,064
And Bond ...

86
00:24:27,038 --> 00:24:30,021
Don't ever break into my house again.

87
00:25:43,002 --> 00:25:46,006
Good day sir,  welcome to the Ocean Club.

88
00:26:04,534 --> 00:26:09,004
Hello? Are you going to take this, or make me wait?

89
00:26:09,034 --> 00:26:11,998
Sorry sir, sorry sir.

90
00:28:33,984 --> 00:28:37,038
Welcome to the Ocean Club sir, checking in?

91
00:28:37,069 --> 00:28:37,949
Yes.

92
00:28:37,979 --> 00:28:41,064
It's a last moment, but do you have a room?

93
00:28:42,985 --> 00:28:46,535
- We have an ocean view villa. - Perfect.

94
00:28:49,913 --> 00:28:56,396
Could you do me a favour, I was at a dinner last night, and I parked my car next to a beautiful 1964 Aston Martin....

95
00:28:56,426 --> 00:28:58,479
- and I'am ashamed to say that I nicked the door and..

96
00:28:58,510 --> 00:29:00,664
Mr. Dimitrios.

97
00:29:01,695 --> 00:29:06,550
If it isn't noticed, I'm not sure I would mention it.

98
00:29:06,591 --> 00:29:10,454
But if I felt contempt to find him..

99
00:29:10,484 --> 00:29:12,699
He has a house just up the beach.

100
00:29:14,216 --> 00:29:15,794
Thank you.

101
00:30:14,777 --> 00:30:17,498
- What? - He is in the Bahamas.

102
00:30:17,538 --> 00:30:19,976
You want to share his holiday plans?

103
00:30:20,016 --> 00:30:23,970
He is logged into our secure web site using your name and password.

104
00:30:24,001 --> 00:30:26,479
How the hell does he know these things?

105
00:30:26,519 --> 00:30:29,907
I'll do my best to find out.

106
00:30:29,948 --> 00:30:33,882
- Who's he looking at? - Alex Dimitrios.

107
00:30:33,912 --> 00:30:35,965
That slimy bugger.

108
00:30:45,877 --> 00:30:47,960
No known associates.

109
00:30:59,095 --> 00:31:00,400
Le Chiffre.

110
00:31:15,965 --> 00:31:18,959
Have a good night club, gentlemen.

111
00:31:20,021 --> 00:31:23,732
- What shall I serve? - Good evening. A vodka martini.

112
00:31:24,956 --> 00:31:26,959
Sharp, big boy.

113
00:31:35,818 --> 00:31:38,751
- Mind if I join you? - Good evening.

114
00:31:49,957 --> 00:31:52,951
- Small blind. Big blind. - I'm in.

115
00:31:55,955 --> 00:31:58,958
That's to you.

116
00:32:00,597 --> 00:32:03,600
If that's for luck, you're twelve late.

117
00:32:11,853 --> 00:32:14,543
- Left to you? - I heard you.

118
00:32:24,940 --> 00:32:27,175
- Check or bet. - Check.

119
00:32:27,206 --> 00:32:29,583
- And you? - 5000.

120
00:32:33,952 --> 00:32:35,954
Five to call.

121
00:32:46,766 --> 00:32:49,709
- Check. - Check to you, sir.

122
00:32:50,831 --> 00:32:52,581
All in.

123
00:32:52,611 --> 00:32:54,907
No, wait.

124
00:32:54,938 --> 00:32:58,943
- 20.000. - Table sticks, I'm sorry sir.

125
00:33:02,432 --> 00:33:06,760
This is on the table. that's my car. You'll bet?

126
00:33:06,801 --> 00:33:08,915
Sorry, mr. Dimitrios.

127
00:33:08,955 --> 00:33:12,596
Please, give him the chance to win his money back.

128
00:33:21,719 --> 00:33:23,944
All right, show me, gentlemen.

129
00:33:28,313 --> 00:33:30,437
Three kings.

130
00:33:37,415 --> 00:33:40,227
Triple aces. Aces win.

131
00:33:44,748 --> 00:33:46,750
Oh, and the valet ticket.

132
00:33:49,936 --> 00:33:51,938
Thank you.

133
00:34:23,938 --> 00:34:26,932
- Thank you. - Thank you, sir.

134
00:34:27,933 --> 00:34:30,937
No wonder he was such a phoney.

135
00:34:31,938 --> 00:34:34,932
- My mistake. - Can I give you a lift home?

136
00:34:34,962 --> 00:34:37,935
Oh that would really send him over the hills.

137
00:34:38,937 --> 00:34:42,932
- I'm afraid I'm not that cruel. - Or you're just out of practice.

138
00:34:49,930 --> 00:34:53,935
- Perhaps. - What about a drink at my place?

139
00:34:53,966 --> 00:34:57,930
Your place? Is it close?

140
00:34:57,961 --> 00:35:00,934
Very.

141
00:35:05,687 --> 00:35:07,650
One drink.

142
00:35:31,922 --> 00:35:35,735
- Good evening sir, and welcome back. - Welcome to my home.

143
00:35:47,922 --> 00:35:53,384
I have a hard time seeing this is my fault. It's your plan, all I did was get you the man.

144
00:35:53,414 --> 00:35:57,409
A man under surveillance by the British Secret Service.

145
00:35:59,604 --> 00:36:04,923
- Which makes me wonder if I can trust you at all. - So don't, I couldn't care less.

146
00:36:04,954 --> 00:36:07,634
But I do care about my reputation.

147
00:36:07,674 --> 00:36:09,920
I have someone else for you to do the job.

148
00:36:09,950 --> 00:36:12,923
He just needs the particulars. And payment.

149
00:36:23,836 --> 00:36:27,720
You like married women, don't you James?

150
00:36:28,509 --> 00:36:30,632
That keeps it simple.

151
00:36:33,636 --> 00:36:36,468
What is it about bad men?

152
00:36:36,498 --> 00:36:39,492
You.. my husband..

153
00:36:39,532 --> 00:36:42,101
I have so many chances to be happy -

154
00:36:42,132 --> 00:36:44,802
- so many nice guys.

155
00:36:44,832 --> 00:36:48,089
Why can't nice guys be more like you?

156
00:36:48,129 --> 00:36:50,799
They would be bad.

157
00:36:55,502 --> 00:36:58,718
But so much more interresting.

158
00:37:02,551 --> 00:37:05,049
What makes your husband a bad man?

159
00:37:05,090 --> 00:37:07,831
His nature, I suppose.

160
00:37:07,861 --> 00:37:13,747
- The nature of his work? - A mystery I'm afraid.

161
00:37:13,788 --> 00:37:19,158
I'm also afraid you sleep with me in order to get to him.

162
00:37:19,188 --> 00:37:23,911
- Are you afraid? - Not enough to stop.

163
00:37:32,063 --> 00:37:35,724
Can I ask you a personal question?

164
00:37:35,755 --> 00:37:39,325
No, won't seem like the properiate time.

165
00:37:39,355 --> 00:37:41,479
Does Ellipsis mean anything to you?

166
00:37:50,844 --> 00:37:56,204
- Should I ask him about it? - Perhaps later.

167
00:37:56,235 --> 00:37:57,984
Yes, dear?

168
00:38:02,263 --> 00:38:06,237
Ok, I understand. See you tomorrow, bye bye.

169
00:38:08,806 --> 00:38:13,297
Apparently, he's on the last flight to Miami.

170
00:38:13,337 --> 00:38:16,877
So you have all night to question me.

171
00:38:20,133 --> 00:38:24,209
In that case we'll need more champagne.

172
00:38:30,904 --> 00:38:33,605
- Good evening, room service. - Good evening.

173
00:38:33,645 --> 00:38:36,366
Can I have a bottle of Bollinger, La Grand Annee -

174
00:38:36,406 --> 00:38:39,572
- And Beluga caviar? - Yes, with everything.

175
00:38:40,209 --> 00:38:42,141
- Would that be for two, sir? - What?

176
00:38:42,171 --> 00:38:44,922
- No, for one.

177
00:39:17,893 --> 00:39:19,774
Wait here.

178
00:41:30,979 --> 00:41:33,740
Hello?

179
00:43:24,657 --> 00:43:26,538
- Yes? - It's Bond.

180
00:43:26,578 --> 00:43:30,492
- I need her now. - I'm afraid she can't be disturbed. Can I take a message?

181
00:43:30,523 --> 00:43:33,881
Listen, you go and find her, tell her to call security at Miami airport , -

182
00:43:33,911 --> 00:43:36,864
- because I think that a bomb is about to go off. Can you do it now?

183
00:43:36,884 --> 00:43:39,028
I can put you on hold.

184
00:43:43,741 --> 00:43:46,341
Bond? What the hell are you up to?

185
00:43:49,193 --> 00:43:50,872
I call you back.

186
00:44:11,291 --> 00:44:14,770
- A Skyfleet S570 prototype. - What about it?

187
00:44:14,811 --> 00:44:17,754
Largest airplane in the world, to be revieled today at Miami airport.

188
00:44:59,331 --> 00:45:00,889
Bond? Bond!

189
00:45:03,437 --> 00:45:06,997
His target is the Skyfleet prototype. It's launching today.

190
00:45:10,750 --> 00:45:11,913
I got to go.

191
00:52:04,066 --> 00:52:08,931
The poll's expired. I'm sorry, I'm not sure how much you've lost

192
00:52:08,961 --> 00:52:12,835
101.206.000 dollars.

193
00:53:03,676 --> 00:53:07,408
Quite a body pile you're stacking up.

194
00:53:07,449 --> 00:53:10,382
She was tortured first...

195
00:53:10,523 --> 00:53:12,526
... as you already killed her husband, she must have been the only one left to question.

196
00:53:13,527 --> 00:53:16,328
- Did she know anyhting compromising? - No.

197
00:53:16,521 --> 00:53:19,322
- Your name, what you're after? - No.

198
00:53:20,222 --> 00:53:25,127
Dimitrios was the middle man, he knew how to put his hands on weapon, and people to use them.

199
00:53:25,319 --> 00:53:27,120
Hw worked for anyone who had money.

200
00:53:27,322 --> 00:53:30,022
He was involved with a man called Le Chiffre, -

201
00:53:30,225 --> 00:53:32,783
- a private banker for the world's terrorists.

202
00:53:32,824 --> 00:53:35,989
He invested their money and gave them access to it wherever they want it.

203
00:53:36,030 --> 00:53:37,527
Og good, you're here.

204
00:53:38,225 --> 00:53:44,323
Albanian we believe, chess protegy, mathematical genious, likes to show it by playing poker.

205
00:54:13,329 --> 00:54:17,526
- So you can keep an eye on me? - Yes.

206
00:54:22,533 --> 00:54:26,285
When they analyzed the stock market up to 9.11, -

207
00:54:26,315 --> 00:54:29,531
- the CIA discovered a massive shortage of airline stocks.

208
00:54:29,734 --> 00:54:33,728
When the stock hit the bottom on 9.11, somebody made a fortune.

209
00:54:33,931 --> 00:54:37,329
The same thing happened this morning with Skyfleet stock, or was supposed to.

210
00:54:37,531 --> 00:54:41,526
With their prototype destroyed, the company would have been a bancrupcy.

211
00:54:41,728 --> 00:54:46,330
Instead, somebody lost over 100 million dollars betting the wrong way.

212
00:54:46,532 --> 00:54:49,020
You think this man was Le Chiffre?

213
00:54:49,051 --> 00:54:53,329
Which would explain how he could set up a high stakes poker game at Casino Royale in Montenegro.

214
00:54:53,531 --> 00:54:57,536
10 players, $10 million buy in, $5 millioner re-buy

215
00:54:57,728 --> 00:55:00,338
Winner takes all, potentially $150 millions.

216
00:55:00,530 --> 00:55:04,980
Good, then we know where he'll be. Do you want a clean kill or do you want to send a message?

217
00:55:05,182 --> 00:55:09,582
We want him alive. Le Chiffre doesn't have a $100 million to loose.

218
00:55:09,784 --> 00:55:13,425
He played the stock market with his client's funds?

219
00:55:13,455 --> 00:55:15,832
They won't be too happy when they find out it's gone.

220
00:55:16,034 --> 00:55:19,928
We can't let him win this game. If he looses, he has nowhere to run.

221
00:55:19,938 --> 00:55:22,932
We'll give him sanfry in return for everything he knows.

222
00:55:23,134 --> 00:55:27,321
I'm putting you in the game. Replacing someone playing for a syndicate.

223
00:55:27,331 --> 00:55:30,335
According to Villiers, you are the best player in the Service.

224
00:55:31,336 --> 00:55:33,531
Thust me, I wish it wasn't the case.

225
00:55:37,536 --> 00:55:41,035
I would ask you if you could remain emotionally detached.

226
00:55:42,138 --> 00:55:46,942
- But I know that's not your problem, is it Boond? - No.

227
00:55:49,834 --> 00:55:53,930
Don't worry about keeping in touch. We know where you are.

228
00:55:53,940 --> 00:55:58,036
You can stop pretending.  You knew I wouldn't let it stop, didn't you?

229
00:55:59,139 --> 00:56:01,141
When I knew you were you.

230
00:56:27,588 --> 00:56:29,591
I am the money.

231
00:56:31,442 --> 00:56:33,444
Every penny of it.

232
00:56:35,042 --> 00:56:38,046
The treasury has agreed to stake you in the game.

233
00:56:38,238 --> 00:56:42,344
Vesper. I hope your parent had it for that.

234
00:56:43,143 --> 00:56:45,085
Thank you.

235
00:56:45,095 --> 00:56:49,940
You must be well connected, I've never seen so much be done so quickly.

236
00:56:49,980 --> 00:56:51,983
Or so stylishly.

237
00:56:53,338 --> 00:56:57,343
- May I ask you where it is? - $10 millions was wired to your account in Montenegro.

238
00:56:57,545 --> 00:57:01,702
With contuingency for 5 more, if I deem it a good looking investment.

239
00:57:02,046 --> 00:57:05,131
I suppose you've given some thought to to the notion that if you loose, -

240
00:57:05,141 --> 00:57:09,469
- our government would have directly financed terrorism.

241
00:57:19,543 --> 00:57:22,546
So you're telling me it's a matter of probability?

242
00:57:22,749 --> 00:57:24,741
I was worried it was some chance involved.

243
00:57:24,943 --> 00:57:27,047
You'll never see the player with the best hand win.

